---
import '../styles/global.css';
import PageNav from '../components/PageNav.astro';
import FourShares from '../components/FourShares.astro';
import UPCollapse from '../components/UPCollapse.astro';
import CumulativeGrowth from '../components/CumulativeGrowth.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;0,9..144,700;0,9..144,800;0,9..144,900;1,9..144,400;1,9..144,600&family=Jost:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Tiro+Devanagari+Hindi:ital@0;1&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>The Consequence · परिणाम · The Indian Census, Part IV</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="page">

      <PageNav current={4} />

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <header class="masthead">
        <div class="masthead-copy">
          <p class="kicker">Part the Fourth · Vol. IV</p>
          <h1 class="title">
            <span class="title-en">The</span>
            <span class="title-en-b">Consequence</span>
            <span class="title-hi">परिणाम</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="lede">
            A case against the arithmetic this paper has just made.
            Before accepting that the Hindi belt has exploded and the South
            restrained itself, read the series again — all of it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="masthead-figure" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="glyph">§</div>
          <div class="figure-no">No.<br /><b>IV</b></div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <section class="chapter-opener">
        <span class="smallcaps">§ the data, reread</span>
        <h2 class="chapter-title">
          <span class="chapter-numeral">v.</span>
          A century, read from 1901
          <span class="chapter-hi hi">एक शताब्दी</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="chapter-lede">
          Three counter-factual figures. Taken from 1901 — when the Census
          of India first became legible at the regional level — the popular
          framing of "North exploded, South restrained itself" does not
          survive contact with the series.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <FourShares />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <UPCollapse />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <CumulativeGrowth />

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <!-- The signed editorial -->
      <section class="editorial">
        <div class="editorial-head">
          <span class="smallcaps">§ an editorial</span>
          <h3 class="editorial-title">
            One person, one vote —
            <em>and the argument that forgets it.</em>
          </h3>
        </div>

        <div class="editorial-body">
          <p>
            The series does not support the premise. Taken from 1901, when
            the Census of India first became legible at the regional level,
            the Hindi belt is the <b>second-fastest-growing</b> of the four
            big regions — barely above the national average, outgrown by
            the West, ahead of the East and South. It is not now, and has
            never been, the runaway the argument requires.
          </p>
          <p>
            UP alone — the state most often named as shorthand for
            &ldquo;unchecked population&rdquo; — <em>shrank</em> between 1901
            and 1921 and has never, since 1901, recovered its share of the
            country. The South grew faster than the North for the first
            half of the twentieth century. The demographic transition the
            argument now cites is a story about the last forty years, not
            about India's demographic history.
          </p>
          <p>
            And if the premise were to stand — that restraint earns weight
            — the logic has somewhere to go that none of its advocates have
            been willing to follow.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="pullquote editorial-pullquote">
          <span class="pullquote-mark" aria-hidden="true">“</span>
          <blockquote class="pullquote-text">
            Why stop at population? Property qualification?
            Literacy test? GDP contribution?
          </blockquote>
          <cite class="pullquote-cite">
            <span class="cite-dash">—</span>
            after
            <a
              href="https://www.indiatoday.in/opinion/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            ><b>Anand Singh</b></a>, <em>India Today</em>, 2025.
            The reductio belongs to him; the data, here, are ours.
          </cite>
        </aside>

        <div class="editorial-body">
          <p>
            That is not federalism. That is the premise of democracy,
            refused. The question worth asking is narrower: whether the
            2026 arithmetic rewards the 1971 choice fairly, whether Finance
            Commission formulas adequately compensate, whether the Rajya
            Sabha's federal balance still holds. Those are real policy
            problems. This report takes no view on them.
          </p>
          <p>
            It takes a view only on the argument that reaches for
            &ldquo;one person, one vote&rdquo; and asks to keep the first
            two words. That argument, on the century of data behind it,
            has nothing to stand on.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="editorial-sign">
          <span class="editorial-dash">—</span>
          <span class="editorial-signoff">
            <b>The Editorial</b>
            <span class="editorial-hi hi">सम्पादकीय टिप्पणी</span>
          </span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <!-- Loop close — back to Page 1 -->
      <aside class="next-step">
        <span class="smallcaps">close the volume</span>
        <a href="/" class="next-link">
          <span class="next-arrow">↻</span>
          <span class="next-title">Return to The Present</span>
          <span class="next-subtitle hi">वर्तमान की ओर</span>
        </a>
        <p class="next-blurb">
          The archive is open. Return to the beginning, or write to the desk.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <footer class="colophon">
        <div class="colophon-col">
          <span class="smallcaps">§ source</span>
          <p>
            Regional population totals from <b>Census of India, Table A-02
            (1901–2011)</b>, NADA catalog 43333. 1881 and 1891 values are
            reconstructions; all counter-factual analysis here uses 1901 as
            the canonical baseline.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="colophon-col">
          <span class="smallcaps">§ after</span>
          <p>
            The satirical reductio (<em>property qualification, literacy
            test, GDP contribution</em>) is owed to Anand Singh, writing in
            India Today in 2025. The argument is paraphrased with
            acknowledgement; the numerical rebuttal is this paper's own.
          </p>
        </div>
      </footer>

      <div class="running-foot">
        <span class="eyebrow">Set in Fraunces &amp; Tiro Devanagari Hindi</span>
        <span class="eyebrow dot">◇</span>
        <span class="eyebrow">Composed on cream</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      import ApexCharts from 'apexcharts';
      import {
        CENSUS,
        REGION_LABELS,
        REGION_COLORS,
        shareSeries,
        cumulativeGrowth,
        cumulativeGrowthIndia,
        type Region,
      } from '../data/census';
      import { STATE_CENSUS, STATE_CENSUS_YEARS } from '../data/state-census';

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Fig. — The arc of four shares, 1901 → 2011
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      const fourRegions: Region[] = ['East', 'West', 'North', 'South'];
      const fourSharesSeries = fourRegions.map((r) => ({
        name: REGION_LABELS[r].en,
        data: shareSeries(r).map((p) => ({ x: String(p.year), y: +p.pct.toFixed(2) })),
      }));

      const fourSharesChart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector('#fourshares-chart')!, {
        chart: {
          type: 'line',
          height: 460,
          fontFamily: '"Jost", "Tiro Devanagari Hindi", system-ui, sans-serif',
          toolbar: { show: false },
          background: 'transparent',
          animations: { enabled: true, speed: 600 },
          parentHeightOffset: 0,
        },
        series: fourSharesSeries,
        colors: fourRegions.map((r) => REGION_COLORS[r]),
        stroke: { width: [2, 2, 3.5, 3.5], curve: 'smooth' },
        markers: { size: 4, strokeWidth: 1, strokeColors: '#1a1510', hover: { size: 7 } },
        dataLabels: { enabled: false },
        xaxis: {
          type: 'category',
          tickAmount: 6,
          labels: { style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#1a1510' } },
          axisBorder: { show: true, color: '#1a1510' },
          axisTicks: { show: false },
          title: { text: 'CENSUS YEAR', style: { fontSize: '10px', color: '#6b5d4f', fontWeight: 500 }, offsetY: 4 },
        },
        yaxis: {
          min: 0,
          max: 50,
          tickAmount: 5,
          labels: {
            formatter: (v: number) => `${v.toFixed(0)}%`,
            style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#6b5d4f' },
          },
          title: { text: '% of India', style: { fontSize: '11px', color: '#6b5d4f', fontWeight: 500 } },
        },
        legend: {
          position: 'top',
          horizontalAlign: 'left',
          fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif',
          fontSize: '12px',
          labels: { colors: '#1a1510' },
          markers: { size: 8, strokeWidth: 1, shape: 'square' },
          itemMargin: { horizontal: 14, vertical: 4 },
          offsetY: -4,
        },
        grid: {
          borderColor: '#d8cdb8',
          strokeDashArray: 2,
          padding: { top: 10, right: 24, bottom: 0, left: 8 },
        },
        annotations: {
          points: [
            {
              x: '1951',
              y: shareSeries('South').find((p) => p.year === 1951)!.pct,
              marker: { size: 5, strokeColor: '#1a1510', fillColor: REGION_COLORS.South, strokeWidth: 1 },
              label: { text: 'South peaks · 26.1%', borderWidth: 0, offsetY: -8,
                style: { color: REGION_COLORS.South, background: 'transparent', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600 } },
            },
            {
              x: '1971',
              y: shareSeries('North').find((p) => p.year === 1971)!.pct,
              marker: { size: 5, strokeColor: '#1a1510', fillColor: REGION_COLORS.North, strokeWidth: 1 },
              label: { text: 'North troughs · 41.9%', borderWidth: 0, offsetY: 24,
                style: { color: REGION_COLORS.North, background: 'transparent', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600 } },
            },
          ],
          yaxis: [
            {
              y: shareSeries('North').find((p) => p.year === 1901)!.pct,
              borderColor: REGION_COLORS.North,
              strokeDashArray: 3,
              borderWidth: 1,
              opacity: 0.4,
              label: { text: "North's 1901 level", borderWidth: 0, offsetY: -4, position: 'left', textAnchor: 'start',
                style: { color: REGION_COLORS.North, background: 'transparent', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', fontSize: '10px', fontWeight: 500 } },
            },
          ],
        },
        tooltip: {
          shared: true,
          intersect: false,
          custom: ({ dataPointIndex, w }) => {
            const year = String(w.globals.categoryLabels[dataPointIndex]);
            const rows = w.globals.series
              .map((s: number[], i: number) => {
                const name = w.globals.seriesNames[i];
                const color = w.globals.colors[i];
                return `<div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:baseline;font-size:12px">
                  <span style="width:8px;height:8px;background:${color};border:1px solid #1a1510;display:inline-block"></span>
                  <span style="flex:1">${name}</span>
                  <b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:14px">${s[dataPointIndex]?.toFixed(1)}%</b>
                </div>`;
              })
              .join('');
            return `<div style="padding:10px 14px;min-width:220px;background:#f5efe3;border:1px solid #1a1510;box-shadow:4px 4px 0 0 #1a1510;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;color:#1a1510">
              <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:700;font-size:16px;margin-bottom:6px;border-bottom:1px solid #1a1510;padding-bottom:4px">${year}</div>
              ${rows}
            </div>`;
          },
        },
      });
      fourSharesChart.render();

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Fig. — UP's share of India, 1901 → 2011
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      const upRow = STATE_CENSUS.find((s) => s.code === 'UP')!;
      const upSeriesData = STATE_CENSUS_YEARS.map((y) => {
        const total = CENSUS.find((r) => r.year === y)!.totalIndiaMillions;
        return { x: String(y), y: +((upRow.values[y] / total) * 100).toFixed(2) };
      });

      const upCollapseChart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector('#upcollapse-chart')!, {
        chart: {
          type: 'area', height: 380,
          fontFamily: '"Jost", "Tiro Devanagari Hindi", system-ui, sans-serif',
          toolbar: { show: false }, background: 'transparent',
          animations: { enabled: true, speed: 600 }, parentHeightOffset: 0,
        },
        series: [{ name: "UP's share of India", data: upSeriesData }],
        colors: [REGION_COLORS.North],
        stroke: { width: 3, curve: 'smooth' },
        fill: {
          type: 'gradient',
          gradient: { shadeIntensity: 0.3, opacityFrom: 0.28, opacityTo: 0.02, stops: [0, 100] },
        },
        markers: { size: 5, strokeWidth: 1, strokeColors: '#1a1510', fillColors: [REGION_COLORS.North], hover: { size: 8 } },
        dataLabels: { enabled: false },
        xaxis: {
          type: 'category',
          labels: { style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#1a1510' } },
          axisBorder: { show: true, color: '#1a1510' }, axisTicks: { show: false },
          title: { text: 'CENSUS YEAR', style: { fontSize: '10px', color: '#6b5d4f', fontWeight: 500 }, offsetY: 4 },
        },
        yaxis: {
          min: 14, max: 22, tickAmount: 4,
          labels: { formatter: (v: number) => `${v.toFixed(0)}%`, style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#6b5d4f' } },
          title: { text: "UP as % of India", style: { fontSize: '11px', color: '#6b5d4f', fontWeight: 500 } },
        },
        legend: { show: false },
        grid: { borderColor: '#d8cdb8', strokeDashArray: 2, padding: { top: 10, right: 24, bottom: 0, left: 8 } },
        annotations: {
          points: [
            {
              x: '1921', y: upSeriesData.find((p) => p.x === '1921')!.y,
              marker: { size: 6, strokeColor: '#1a1510', fillColor: '#8c2e1a', strokeWidth: 1 },
              label: { text: "1901 → 1921 · −4.5%", borderWidth: 0, offsetY: 26,
                style: { color: '#8c2e1a', background: 'transparent', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600 } },
            },
            {
              x: '1971', y: upSeriesData.find((p) => p.x === '1971')!.y,
              marker: { size: 6, strokeColor: '#1a1510', fillColor: '#8c2e1a', strokeWidth: 1 },
              label: { text: "1971 trough · 15.3%", borderWidth: 0, offsetY: 24,
                style: { color: '#8c2e1a', background: 'transparent', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600 } },
            },
          ],
          yaxis: [
            {
              y: upSeriesData.find((p) => p.x === '1901')!.y,
              borderColor: '#6b5d4f', strokeDashArray: 3, borderWidth: 1, opacity: 0.5,
              label: { text: "1901 level · 19.6%", borderWidth: 0, offsetY: -4, position: 'left', textAnchor: 'start',
                style: { color: '#6b5d4f', background: 'transparent', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', fontSize: '10px', fontWeight: 500 } },
            },
          ],
        },
        tooltip: {
          custom: ({ dataPointIndex }: any) => {
            const p = upSeriesData[dataPointIndex];
            const abs = upRow.values[Number(p.x)];
            return `<div style="padding:10px 14px;min-width:200px;background:#f5efe3;border:1px solid #1a1510;box-shadow:4px 4px 0 0 #1a1510;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;color:#1a1510">
              <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:700;font-size:16px;margin-bottom:6px;border-bottom:1px solid #1a1510;padding-bottom:4px">${p.x}</div>
              <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;font-size:12px"><span>UP population</span><b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:14px">${abs.toFixed(1)}M</b></div>
              <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px"><span>Share of India</span><b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:14px">${p.y.toFixed(2)}%</b></div>
            </div>`;
          },
        },
      });
      upCollapseChart.render();

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Fig. — Cumulative % growth by region, 1901 → 2011
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      const cumRegions: Region[] = ['West', 'North', 'East', 'South'];
      const cumShortLabel: Record<Region, string> = {
        East: 'East', West: 'West', North: 'North', South: 'South', Other: 'Other',
      };
      const cumulativeData = cumRegions
        .map((r) => ({
          region: r, name: REGION_LABELS[r].en, shortName: cumShortLabel[r],
          pct: +cumulativeGrowth(r).toFixed(1),
        }))
        .sort((a, b) => b.pct - a.pct);
      const nationalCum = +cumulativeGrowthIndia().toFixed(1);

      const cumChart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector('#cumulative-chart')!, {
        chart: {
          type: 'bar', height: 340,
          fontFamily: '"Jost", "Tiro Devanagari Hindi", system-ui, sans-serif',
          toolbar: { show: false }, background: 'transparent', parentHeightOffset: 0,
        },
        series: [{ name: 'Cumulative growth', data: cumulativeData.map((d) => ({ x: d.shortName, y: d.pct })) }],
        colors: cumulativeData.map((d) => REGION_COLORS[d.region]),
        plotOptions: {
          bar: { horizontal: true, barHeight: '64%', borderRadius: 0, distributed: true, dataLabels: { position: 'top' } },
        },
        stroke: { show: true, width: 0.5, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        dataLabels: {
          enabled: true,
          formatter: (v: number) => `${v.toFixed(0)}%`,
          offsetX: 28,
          style: { fontSize: '12px', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontWeight: 700, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        },
        xaxis: {
          labels: { formatter: (v: string) => `${Number(v).toFixed(0)}%`,
            style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#6b5d4f' } },
          axisBorder: { show: true, color: '#1a1510' }, axisTicks: { show: false },
          title: { text: 'CUMULATIVE % GROWTH, 1901 → 2011', style: { fontSize: '10px', color: '#6b5d4f', fontWeight: 500 }, offsetY: 4 },
        },
        yaxis: {
          labels: { style: { fontSize: '12px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#1a1510', fontWeight: 500 } },
        },
        legend: { show: false },
        grid: { borderColor: '#d8cdb8', strokeDashArray: 2, xaxis: { lines: { show: true } }, yaxis: { lines: { show: false } }, padding: { top: 0, right: 44, bottom: 0, left: 8 } },
        annotations: {
          xaxis: [
            {
              x: nationalCum, borderColor: '#8c2e1a', strokeDashArray: 4, borderWidth: 1.5,
              label: { text: `national · ${nationalCum.toFixed(0)}%`, orientation: 'horizontal', position: 'top', offsetY: -6, borderWidth: 0,
                style: { color: '#8c2e1a', background: '#f5efe3', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontSize: '11px', fontWeight: 600, padding: { left: 6, right: 6, top: 2, bottom: 2 } } },
            },
          ],
        },
        tooltip: {
          custom: ({ dataPointIndex }: any) => {
            const d = cumulativeData[dataPointIndex];
            const color = REGION_COLORS[d.region];
            return `<div style="padding:12px 14px;min-width:220px;background:#f5efe3;border:1px solid #1a1510;box-shadow:4px 4px 0 0 #1a1510;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;color:#1a1510">
              <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:6px">
                <span style="width:10px;height:10px;background:${color};border:1px solid #1a1510;display:inline-block"></span>
                <span style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:700;font-size:15px">${d.name}</span>
              </div>
              <div style="border-top:1px solid #1a1510;padding-top:6px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px">
                <div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#6b5d4f;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.14em">growth</div><b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:22px">${d.pct.toFixed(1)}%</b></div>
                <div><div style="font-size:10px;color:#6b5d4f;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.14em">vs. India</div><b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:22px;color:${d.pct > nationalCum ? '#8c2e1a' : '#1f4d54'}">${d.pct > nationalCum ? '+' : ''}${(d.pct - nationalCum).toFixed(1)}pp</b></div>
              </div>
            </div>`;
          },
        },
      });
      cumChart.render();

      requestAnimationFrame(() => { document.body.classList.add('ready'); });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
